cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.NI, cs.MM

Reasoning: The paper discusses transmission over different types of channels using M-ary orthogonal FSK or OOFSK, which are techniques commonly used in communication systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.COMM (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also considers the impact of fading on energy efficiency, which falls under the sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the use of hard-decision detection and the investigation of energy requirements for sending one bit of information suggest relevance to cs.NI (Networking and Information Security) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
